# Narrow exception: Sprint-6 T13 fixture pack ships a deliberately-public
# RSA public-key PEM used to verify the static AgentCard JWS in
# `tests/unit/protocol/test_a2a_fixture_pack_admission.py`. The
# corresponding private key was generated at fixture-author time and
# discarded — only the .pub.pem (which is, by definition, public) is
# tracked. The `*.pem` rule above remains in force for every other path.
!tests/fixtures/cognic_test_agent_pack/cognic_test_agent_pack/agent_cards/test_agent.pub.pem

# Sprint-7A T14 narrow exception: cli/sign.py + cli/verify.py task-local
# fixture pack ships an explicit test-only RSA keypair (BOTH private +
# public PEM committed) used by T14's JWS-signing arm + T14's verify
# happy-path arm to deterministically regenerate + verify the AgentCard
# JWS in-process. Per R9 P2 #1 the private key is committed (mirrors
# the Sprint-6 fixture-pack public-PEM pattern but on the private side):
#  - the keypair is synthetic, no production trust root anywhere trusts it
#  - the prod settings profile rejects ``signing_key_path`` paths under
#    ``tests/fixtures/`` or ``examples/`` at startup (config.py:966)
#  - the ``test_signing_key`` naming + the NOTE.md alongside both PEMs
#    make the test-only intent unmissable
# The `*.pem` rule above remains in force for every other path.
!tests/fixtures/cli_sign_target_pack/attestations/test-signing/test_signing_key.private.pem
!tests/fixtures/cli_sign_target_pack/attestations/test-signing/test_signing_key.public.pem
# Sprint-7A T15: same rationale as the T14 fixture pair above; this
# pair lives under examples/cognic-agent-example-minimal/ so the T15
# reference-pack lifecycle test can deterministically sign + verify
# the AgentCard JWS without live signing infrastructure. See
# examples/cognic-agent-example-minimal/attestations/test-signing/NOTE.md
# for the full rationale + audit trail.
!examples/cognic-agent-example-minimal/attestations/test-signing/test_signing_key.private.pem
!examples/cognic-agent-example-minimal/attestations/test-signing/test_signing_key.public.pem

# Proof 1a: the in-process harness + authoring helper run real `agentos sign`
# against examples/cognic-tool-search/, which writes generated attestations
# here (like its `dist/` sibling, caught by the generic `dist/` rule above).
# Never commit them.
examples/cognic-tool-search/attestations/

# Build artefacts (Sprint 4+ supply chain bundles, ignored from CI checkouts)
attestations/local/

# Editor sandboxes / agent worktrees
# Track shared Claude Code configuration (settings.json + hook scripts);
# ignore everything else under .claude/ (session caches, project state, etc.)
.claude/*
!.claude/settings.json
!.claude/hooks/

# Docker artefacts
.docker/

# Proof 1b-2c (M3-E2c): transient build-context copies the operator runner
# (infra/proof-1b-2c/run-proof-1b-2c.sh) materialises then removes on exit (trap).
# Gitignored defensively so an interrupted run never leaves them stageable.
infra/proof-1b-2c/proof1b2c-staging/
infra/proof-1b-2c/proof_1b_2c/
infra/proof-1b-2c/_local_as.py

# Proof M4 (operator-install): transient build-context copies the operator runner
# (infra/proof-m4/run-proof-m4.sh) materialises then removes on exit (trap).
# Gitignored defensively so an interrupted run never leaves them stageable.
infra/proof-m4/proof-m4-staging/
infra/proof-m4/proof_m4/
infra/proof-m4/_local_as.py
